  <eligibility>
    <criteria>
      <textblock>
        Inclusion Criteria:

          -  ≥ 18 years

          -  Abscess ≤ 5cm in diameter

          -  Truncal or extremity location

        Exclusion Criteria:

          -  Post-operative abscess (abscess in location of operative incision, operation within
             the last 4 months)

          -  HIV/immunocompromised/transplant recipient/chronic oral steroid use

          -  Fever at triage (temp ≥38 degrees Celsius)

          -  Abscess secondary to Crohn's

          -  Multiple abscesses requiring drainage

          -  Prior participation in the study for the same abscess

          -  Incision and drainage performed with no packing required, or where abscess cavity is
             &lt;1 cm max diameter

          -  Bartholins/perigenital, perianal, or facial abscesses

          -  Complicated abscesses (fistula, suspicion of muscular extension, consultation/direct
             referral to general surgery)

          -  Inability to give consent
      </textblock>
    </criteria>
